{
  "texts": [
    "Our work highlights the necessity for educators to critically evaluate and supplement AI-generated content, ensuring that students are guided correctly and threats affecting LLM performance are effectively addressed (Lopez-Gazpio, 2024).",
    "Recently, the surge in GAI tools has significantly influenced educational paradigms, offering personalized learning experiences, tailored feedback, and additional resources for classroom instruction.",
    "The widespread application of these technologies across diverse educational fields, underscored by the advent of OpenAI's ChatGPT, has sparked discussions on their role in academic integrity and the assessment process.",
    "Despite the broad applicability of LLMs across disciplines, their specific impact on chemistry education requires closer examination, particularly regarding ChatGPT's ability to handle chemistry-related assessments.",
    "Several studies (Clark, 2023; Emenike & Emenike, 2023; Fergus et al., 2023; Humphry & Fuller, 2023; Tyson, 2023) have embarked on an evaluation of Chat-GPT's proficiency within the chemistry domain, aiming to delineate its operational strengths and weaknesses."
  ]
}